msgid "I didn't change anything!"
msgstr "I didn't change anything!"

#: ../../I/I-didn-t-change-anything-.rst:7
msgid "interj\\."
msgstr "間投詞"

#: ../../I/I-didn-t-change-anything-.rst:9
msgid ""
"An aggrieved cry often heard as bugs manifest during a regression test. The "
":ref:`canonical` reply to this assertion is \"Then it works just the same as"
" it did before, doesn't it?\" See also :ref:`one-line-fix`\\. This is also "
"heard from applications programmers trying to blame an obvious applications "
"problem on an unrelated systems software change, for example a divide-by-0 "
"fault after terminals were added to a network. Usually, their statement is "
"found to be false. Upon close questioning, they will admit some major "
"restructuring of the program that shouldn't have broken anything, in their "
"opinion, but which actually :ref:`hosed` the code completely."
msgstr ""
"リグレッションテスト中にバグが現れたときによく聞かれる、悲痛な叫び。この主張に対する\\ :ref:`canonical`\\ "
"な返答は「では、以前とまったく同じように動いているわけだね?」である。\\ :ref:`one-line-fix`\\ "
"も参照。これは、明らかにアプリケーション側の問題を、無関係なシステムソフトウェアの変更のせいにしようとするアプリケーションプログラマからもよく聞かれる。たとえば、ネットワークに端末を追加した後でゼロ除算のフォルトが起きた、というように。たいていの場合、彼らの主張は誤りであることが判明する。よく問い詰めてみると、彼らは自分の考えでは何も壊すはずのなかったプログラムの大幅な再構築を行ったことを認めるのだが、それが実際にはコードを完全に\\"
" :ref:`hosed`\\ にしていたのである。"
